-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-WestJet Airlines, Sirius XM Canada
-- 
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 06:28AM EDT
-- None



July 15 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including WestJet and Air Canada, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Sirius XM Canada <XSR.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$9.50 from C$9  * Intertain Group <IT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from spec buy; target to C$8 * WestJet Airlines <WJA.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$30 from C$29; buy   Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.* Air Canada <ACb.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$12 from C$11.50; buy  * Gluskin Sheff + Associates <GS.TO>:Canaccord Genuity ups target to C$34 from C$33.25; hold * Intertain Group <IT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from spec buy; target to C$8  * Lake Shore Gold <LSG.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$1.50 from C$1  * Paramount Resources <POU.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$72.50 from C$65  * Sirius XM Canada <XSR.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$9.50 from C$9  * Tricon Capital Group <TCN.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$10; rating buy